WEBVTT

00:00.668 --> 00:02.903
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:20.788 --> 00:23.691
♪♪

00:26.394 --> 00:28.162
[ Chomping ]

00:28.196 --> 00:31.632
[ Slurping ]

00:31.665 --> 00:37.305
[ Pop! ]

00:37.338 --> 00:38.939
Mom!

00:41.209 --> 00:42.276
Mm-mm.

00:42.310 --> 00:43.344
Mm?

00:43.377 --> 00:45.246
Mm-mm-mm-mm.

00:45.279 --> 00:47.481
No, I didn't get
a new haircut.

00:47.515 --> 00:48.482
Hmm.

00:48.516 --> 00:49.483
[ Gasps ]

00:49.517 --> 00:50.584
Hmm?

00:50.618 --> 00:53.020
Hmm, hmm, hmm!

00:53.053 --> 00:55.123
No, I'm not desperately
trying to get noticed

00:55.156 --> 00:56.557
for waxing my mustache.

00:56.590 --> 00:57.591
Hmm!

00:57.625 --> 00:59.393
[ Gasps, squeak ]

00:59.427 --> 01:01.429
No, I haven't had my
dentures whitened,

01:01.462 --> 01:02.696
and I don't wear dentures!

01:02.730 --> 01:04.165
And by the way,
I can plainly see

01:04.198 --> 01:06.434
you're all miming,
so just man up and ask.

01:06.467 --> 01:07.601
[ Inhales sharply ]

01:07.635 --> 01:08.802
What did we do wrong?!
[ Whines ]

01:08.836 --> 01:10.804
It might be that
a certain someone

01:10.838 --> 01:12.873
forgot a certain something.

01:12.906 --> 01:15.042
Uh, you're being a bit
hypocritical here.

01:15.075 --> 01:17.478
You can't be angry at someone
for forgetting something

01:17.511 --> 01:20.281
if you can't even remember
their name or what they forgot.

01:20.314 --> 01:21.482
[ Inhales ]

01:21.515 --> 01:25.186
It's fine. No need to make
a fuss about it.

01:27.688 --> 01:29.523
I got it.

01:29.557 --> 01:32.793
There must be some secret fuss
that I shouldn't know about!

01:32.826 --> 01:34.795
No, there is no fuss.

01:34.828 --> 01:36.264
[Chuckles ] No fuss.
Got it.

01:36.297 --> 01:37.965
No, seriously,
there is no fuss.

01:37.998 --> 01:39.767
you just said
you didn't want a fuss.

01:39.800 --> 01:41.402
Also, what is all
this fuss about?

01:41.435 --> 01:44.238
Sure, you didn't
organize any fuss.

01:44.272 --> 01:46.640
I'm not bluffing.
There's no fussing.

01:46.674 --> 01:47.975
[ Doorbell rings ]

01:48.008 --> 01:50.644
[ Gasps ] Oh!
I wonder who this could be!

01:50.678 --> 01:53.481
Oh!
A sing-a-gram!

01:53.514 --> 01:55.082
Uh...

01:55.115 --> 01:56.917
♪ Hello, my darling
Hello, my baby ♪

01:56.950 --> 01:58.986
♪ This is from the IRS

01:59.019 --> 02:01.355
♪ You better pay it,
they're getting serious ♪

02:01.389 --> 02:04.392
♪ Your home
will be repossessed ♪

02:04.425 --> 02:05.793
There you go.

02:05.826 --> 02:07.795
What?

02:07.828 --> 02:09.897
[ Gasps ]
A party!

02:09.930 --> 02:11.432
I knew it.

02:11.465 --> 02:12.566
Yay!

02:12.600 --> 02:13.667
[ Feet squealing ]

02:13.701 --> 02:15.269
[ Funeral song playing ]

02:15.303 --> 02:17.571
Even acupuncture
couldn't save him.

02:20.474 --> 02:22.042
[ Sighs ]

02:22.075 --> 02:23.944
[ Airplane buzzing overhead ]

02:23.977 --> 02:27.181
"It's a special day!"

02:27.215 --> 02:29.283
Aww!

02:29.317 --> 02:33.721
"Get 25% off at Dave's
Skywriting Emporium"?

02:33.754 --> 02:38.759
Wait, so you really haven't
organized anything?

02:38.792 --> 02:39.760
Oh.

02:39.793 --> 02:42.796
Okay.

02:42.830 --> 02:44.232
It's all right.

02:44.265 --> 02:46.634
It's quite all right,
really.

02:46.667 --> 02:48.636
Don't make a fuss.

02:48.669 --> 02:50.538
Okay, then.

02:50.571 --> 02:51.839
[ Sighs ]

02:51.872 --> 02:53.841
Something about
her body language

02:53.874 --> 02:55.409
tells me
she doesn't mean that.

02:56.344 --> 02:57.745
Yep. Pack your bags,
we're about to go on

02:57.778 --> 02:59.380
the round-the-world
guilt trip.

02:59.413 --> 03:02.516
Unless we figure out what we
should be making a fuss about.

03:05.319 --> 03:07.555
[ Sighs ]

03:09.557 --> 03:11.992
[ Wind whistling ]

03:12.025 --> 03:14.595
[ Thunder booms ]

03:16.297 --> 03:19.600
♪ Dirty socks
and filthy clothes ♪

03:19.633 --> 03:23.404
♪ When all I wanted
was a sweet red rose ♪

03:23.437 --> 03:30.444
♪ And how could anyone forget
or fail to see why I'm upset ♪

03:30.478 --> 03:34.582
♪ He made me laugh
with things he said ♪

03:34.615 --> 03:37.551
♪ But now he can't
remember the day we -- ♪

03:37.585 --> 03:39.920
[ Electricity crackles,
music stops ]

03:39.953 --> 03:42.189
Aaaah! Gumball!
Put out the fire!

03:42.222 --> 03:43.424
Ahh!

03:43.457 --> 03:44.858
No, don't!

03:44.892 --> 03:47.395
Aah!

03:47.428 --> 03:49.497
Pwah! The song!
Finish the song!

03:49.530 --> 03:52.700
No. A certain someone should
know why today is important.

03:52.733 --> 03:54.602
Why did you say we shouldn't be
making a fuss

03:54.635 --> 03:56.504
if you get all angry about it
when we don't?

03:56.537 --> 03:58.506
"No need to make a fuss"
is a thing people say,

03:58.539 --> 04:00.073
but they obviously
don't mean it.

04:00.107 --> 04:02.543
It's all in the subtext,
like when someone says,

04:02.576 --> 04:04.011
"I'm only two minutes away."

04:05.178 --> 04:07.047
"But we should
stay in touch."

04:08.115 --> 04:10.217
Or, "It's fine, honey."

04:11.519 --> 04:12.886
Uh, okay.

04:12.920 --> 04:14.955
So, are you gonna tell us what
we should be celebrating?

04:14.988 --> 04:17.658
Don't worry about it,
sweetheart.

04:19.493 --> 04:22.195
It's kind of difficult
to organize a party

04:22.229 --> 04:23.230
if we don't know
what it's for.

04:23.263 --> 04:24.565
What's appropriate?
Cake?

04:24.598 --> 04:26.500
What if it's the anniversary
of some tragedy?

04:26.534 --> 04:27.535
A black cake?

04:27.568 --> 04:29.069
Let's keep it
as vague as possible.

04:29.102 --> 04:30.804
Like this, look.
"Today's the day."

04:30.838 --> 04:32.806
Do I draw a smiley face
on the card or not?

04:32.840 --> 04:34.575
Make it both!

04:34.608 --> 04:35.943
[ Scribbling ]

04:37.878 --> 04:38.846
Mm.

04:38.879 --> 04:40.781
Keep it neutral.

04:40.814 --> 04:42.115
[ Balloon expands ]

04:42.149 --> 04:43.751
Good choice! Beige,
the Wednesday of colors.

04:43.784 --> 04:46.320
Like a visual muzak.
As noncommittal as can be.

04:46.354 --> 04:47.721
Okay, I'll be Mom coming in.

04:47.755 --> 04:50.924
Everyone, try and look
as bland as possible.

04:50.958 --> 04:53.026
[ Gasps ]

04:53.060 --> 04:54.628
I feel nothing.
It's perfect.

04:54.662 --> 04:56.096
[ Door opens ]
[ Gasps ] She's coming!

04:56.129 --> 04:59.600
Get ready to sing
the everything song!

04:59.633 --> 05:01.402
[ Gasps ]

05:01.435 --> 05:04.872
♪ Today's so very important,
it doesn't come very often ♪

05:04.905 --> 05:06.840
♪ For reasons you thought
we'd forgotten ♪

05:06.874 --> 05:08.442
♪ Today is all about you

05:08.476 --> 05:12.279
♪ It's such an important day
It's such an important day ♪

05:12.312 --> 05:15.416
♪ Happy today to you,
happy today to you ♪

05:15.449 --> 05:19.086
♪ Happy today, dear Nicole

05:19.119 --> 05:22.990
♪ Unless it's kind of sad, too

05:23.023 --> 05:25.192
♪ This day for you

05:25.225 --> 05:28.429
♪ Is important for us, too

05:28.462 --> 05:30.564
♪ A sad and serious day

05:30.598 --> 05:35.068
♪ unless you want us
to say hooray ♪

05:35.102 --> 05:36.604
♪ We know this idea
is not strong ♪

05:36.637 --> 05:38.238
♪ This is clearly
a Christmas song ♪

05:38.271 --> 05:40.073
♪ We can't keep this up
for too long ♪

05:40.107 --> 05:43.176
♪ So tell us what's wrong

05:46.714 --> 05:50.083
"With deepest feelings
on this momentous occasion."

05:50.117 --> 05:52.219
Smooth.
[ Panting ]

05:52.252 --> 05:55.022
We baked you a cake.

05:55.055 --> 05:56.624
Really?

06:00.694 --> 06:02.763
[ Splat! ]

06:02.796 --> 06:04.665
Dad, she was looking you
right in the eye.

06:04.698 --> 06:06.233
It's you who's
forgotten something!

06:06.266 --> 06:07.267
What is it?

06:07.300 --> 06:09.236
Okay. Let me think.

06:10.671 --> 06:12.139
[ All gasp ]

06:12.172 --> 06:14.875
[ Panting ]

06:14.908 --> 06:16.243
What's going on?

06:16.276 --> 06:18.078
[ Mumbling incoherently ]

06:18.111 --> 06:21.682
I think he's
using his brain!

06:21.715 --> 06:22.683
[ Roars ]

06:22.716 --> 06:23.817
This is dangerous!

06:23.851 --> 06:25.953
He's pushing way past
his usual limits!

06:25.986 --> 06:28.722
[ Yelling ]

06:28.756 --> 06:31.058
Aaaah!

06:31.091 --> 06:32.159
Aaaah!

06:32.192 --> 06:33.326
Aaaah!

06:33.360 --> 06:36.764
Ooh! Ooh! Ooh!

06:36.797 --> 06:38.566
He's not gonna make it!

06:38.599 --> 06:41.735
No, Darwin.
He has to do this.

06:41.769 --> 06:44.538
Aaaaah!

06:45.939 --> 06:47.040
[ Gasps ]

06:47.074 --> 06:48.175
I got it.

06:48.208 --> 06:49.242
What is it?

06:49.276 --> 06:50.711
We ask for a clue!

06:50.744 --> 06:52.179
[ Groaning ]

06:52.212 --> 06:54.715
[ Pounding ]

06:54.748 --> 06:57.885
Can you please just tell us why
today is so special

06:57.918 --> 06:59.553
so this family can
get back to functioning

06:59.587 --> 07:00.921
in its usual
dysfunctional way?

07:00.954 --> 07:05.759
[ Sighs ] It's November 1.
Our wedding anniversary.

07:11.665 --> 07:15.002
Hmm.

07:15.035 --> 07:17.905
Since when do swans
have nipples?

07:17.938 --> 07:20.340
[ Bawling ]

07:20.373 --> 07:22.876
Dad, there's only one way
to save the day --

07:22.910 --> 07:24.144
with a totally over-the-top,

07:24.177 --> 07:25.646
disproportionate,
overblown gesture.

07:25.679 --> 07:27.314
[ Sniffle ]
You're right!

07:27.347 --> 07:29.883
I don't know what's so special
about October 11,

07:29.917 --> 07:32.319
but I know it's an important day
to your mother,

07:32.352 --> 07:35.756
so I'm going to make sure
I never forget it again.

07:35.789 --> 07:36.857
How?

07:36.890 --> 07:38.859
Hmm.

07:38.892 --> 07:42.963
That's not a swan.
It's an elephant.

07:42.996 --> 07:44.164
What are you
talking about?

07:44.197 --> 07:45.499
Well, didn't you ever wonder

07:45.533 --> 07:47.501
why we went on summer vacation
in January?

07:47.535 --> 07:49.202
The calendar
was upside down.

07:49.236 --> 07:52.272
Today is October 11,
not November 1.

07:52.305 --> 07:54.041
[ Gasps ]

07:54.074 --> 07:58.478
I'm going to get a tattoo of
October 11 on my butt!

07:58.512 --> 08:00.881
Okay, a tattoo
is a big commitment.

08:00.914 --> 08:03.150
You should probably
think about it for --

08:03.183 --> 08:04.585
[ Horn honks ]

08:04.618 --> 08:07.821
So, it turns out I was...
[ Mumbles ]

08:07.855 --> 08:08.789
What?

08:08.822 --> 08:11.258
You know, I was...
[ Mumbles ]

08:11.291 --> 08:12.626
[ Sighs ]
She thought today was

08:12.660 --> 08:14.461
their wedding anniversary,
but it isn't.

08:14.494 --> 08:16.163
She's trying to say
she was wrong,

08:16.196 --> 08:18.666
but her mouth is pathologically
incapable of saying those words.

08:18.699 --> 08:21.134
Well, I hope her legs are
capable of making up for it.

08:21.168 --> 08:23.336
What? Why?

08:23.370 --> 08:25.906
It looks just like her.

08:25.939 --> 08:27.174
Thanks.

08:29.376 --> 08:31.745
I'd like this on that.

08:31.779 --> 08:33.146
Uh-huh.

08:33.180 --> 08:34.915
[ All panting ]

08:36.550 --> 08:38.351
[ Tires screeching ]

08:38.385 --> 08:40.287
[ Crash! ]

08:40.320 --> 08:41.521
What are you doing?

08:41.555 --> 08:43.123
I couldn't see ahead!

08:43.156 --> 08:45.593
Then we're gonna
have to run.

08:46.794 --> 08:49.062
Ow! It hurts so bad!

08:49.096 --> 08:51.164
Oh, no, no, no!
I can't do it!

08:51.198 --> 08:52.866
It's too painful!

08:52.900 --> 08:56.369
Dude, I assure you, that's a
reasonable price for a tattoo.

09:04.077 --> 09:05.579
[ Honk! ]

09:05.613 --> 09:07.414
Ahh, please don't be a butt,
please don't be a butt,

09:07.447 --> 09:08.415
please don't be a butt.

09:08.448 --> 09:10.718
Oh, thank you, universe.

09:10.751 --> 09:11.985
[ Shivering ]

09:12.019 --> 09:14.988
Technically,
that's my face.

09:16.289 --> 09:18.792
Uhh, that's my butt.
[ Sighs ]

09:18.826 --> 09:19.960
Let's go this way!

09:19.993 --> 09:22.295
We can see where we're going
in this direction!

09:23.396 --> 09:24.564
[ Needle buzzing ]

09:24.598 --> 09:25.599
Wait!

09:25.633 --> 09:28.301
What?
You're holding it upside down.

09:28.335 --> 09:29.737
[ Laughs ]

09:29.770 --> 09:31.271
Almost got
the date wrong there.

09:31.304 --> 09:33.140
[ Both laugh ]

09:33.173 --> 09:34.441
Where is it?

09:34.474 --> 09:36.509
By the strip mall,
somewhere on the left.

09:36.543 --> 09:38.111
I can't see anything!

09:38.145 --> 09:39.847
[ Grunts ]

09:39.880 --> 09:42.282
Oh.
Oh, my gosh, I'm so sorry.

09:42.315 --> 09:45.953
Wait, I gotta write you a ticket
before I forget what happened.

09:49.156 --> 09:50.658
[ Splat! ]

09:56.396 --> 09:58.198
Stop!
[ Needle stops ]

09:58.231 --> 10:00.100
What?
Where's my husband?

10:00.133 --> 10:02.202
I'm here!

10:02.235 --> 10:04.938
Oh, here.

10:06.439 --> 10:07.374
What have you done?

10:07.407 --> 10:09.442
Ahh, don't worry, honey.

10:09.476 --> 10:11.879
Oh, thank goodness.
You didn't go through with it.

10:11.912 --> 10:14.014
No, I totally
went through with it.

10:14.047 --> 10:15.783
I just meant that
he gave me a discount

10:15.816 --> 10:18.351
so you don't need to worry
about the price.

10:20.120 --> 10:21.421
Oh, Richard.

10:21.454 --> 10:23.323
Now I'll never forget
what day it is.

10:23.356 --> 10:25.325
I will always look
at this and think,

10:25.358 --> 10:29.362
"I wonder what day that is,"
forever.

10:29.396 --> 10:31.298
But I was wro...
[ Mumbles ]

10:31.331 --> 10:32.700
Huh?

10:32.733 --> 10:34.234
She messed up with the date
and she was wrong.

10:34.267 --> 10:35.703
[ Gasps ]

10:35.736 --> 10:37.204
[ Laughs ]

10:37.237 --> 10:40.307
Well, that's a day
to remember.

10:40.340 --> 10:43.376
[ Grunts ]
Aw! Just kidding.

10:43.410 --> 10:46.680
I know exactly
how to fix this.

10:46.714 --> 10:47.981
How?

10:48.015 --> 10:50.217
[ Tattoo needle buzzing ]

10:50.250 --> 10:54.554
Now I'll never forget to
think about you every day.

10:54.587 --> 10:56.056
What do you think?

10:56.089 --> 10:57.324
Hmm.

10:57.357 --> 10:59.760
I love it.
